Package net.marfgamer.jraknet.client

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    RakNetClientListener
    This interface is used by the RakNetClient to let the user know when specific events are triggered.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MaximumTransferUnit
    Used by the RakNetClient during login to track how and when it should modify it's maximum transfer unit in the login process.
    RakNetClient
    Used to connect to servers using the RakNet protocol.
    RakNetClientHandler
    Used by the RakNetClient with the sole purpose of sending received packets to the client so they can be handled.
    SessionPreparation
    Used by the RakNetClient to easily store data during login and create the session when the client is connected.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AlreadyConnectedException
    Signals that a RakNetClient is attempting to connect to a server that it is already connected to.
    ConnectionBannedException
    Signals that a RakNetClient's connection is banned from the server.
    IncompatibleProtocolException
    Signals that a RakNetClient does not share the same protocol as the server it is attempting to connect to.
    LoginFailureException
    Signals that the RakNetClient experienced an error during the login process.
    NettyHandlerException
    Signals that a Throwable was caught by the RakNetClientHandler.
    NoFreeIncomingConnectionsException
    Signals that the server the RakNetClient is attempting to connect to is full.
    PacketBufferException
    Signals that a packet critical to the RakNetClient failed to encode or decode correctly.
    RakNetClientException
    Represents an exception specific to the RakNetClient
    ServerOfflineException
    Signals that a RakNetClient is attempting to connect to an offline server.
